## AnimatePresence Rules

Wrap **every** conditional render that should animate in/out:

```tsx
import { AnimatePresence, motion } from 'framer-motion'

<AnimatePresence initial={false}>
  {isVisible && (
    <motion.div
      key="unique-stable-key"   // ← required. must not change between renders
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 10 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      exit={{ opacity: 0, y: 6 }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.2, ease: [0, 0, 0.2, 1] }}
    >
      {children}
    </motion.div>
  )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

| `mode` | Use when |
|--------|----------|
| default | List items, tooltips, badges — siblings animate independently |
| `mode="wait"` | Page/tab transitions — old exits before new enters |
| `mode="popLayout"` | Reordering lists — siblings shift smoothly to fill gaps |

**Rule**: Always provide an `exit` variant. An element that just pops out of existence is a bug.

