## Motion Checklist

### Before Writing
- [ ] Is this motion communicating something (state change, relationship, sequence) or just decorating?
- [ ] Would removing this animation confuse the user? If not, reconsider it.

### During Implementation
- [ ] `ease.out` on enter, `ease.in` on exit — never `linear`
- [ ] Duration ≤ 200ms for element entry/exit, ≤ 300ms for panels/modals
- [ ] `AnimatePresence` wraps every conditional render that animates
- [ ] Stable `key` on every `AnimatePresence` child
- [ ] `exit` variant defined — elements never just disappear
- [ ] `useReducedMotion()` check — remove y/scale when true, keep opacity

### Post-Implementation
- [ ] Does it feel instant enough? (if it feels slow, halve the duration)
- [ ] Do 3+ things animate simultaneously? If yes, sequence them instead
- [ ] Test with `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` in browser DevTools

